<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4581403>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. SEM micrographs of Syllidia armata from Sweden. (A) Anterior end, dorsal view; (B) anterior end, ventral view of subadult specimen (22 segments) with neuropodial lobes and chaetae on segment 3; (C) distal part of everted proboscis, ventral view, with papillae embedded in cilia. The two visible folds (arrows) will extend to form the ventral incision in the fully everted proboscis; (D) anterior end, ventro-lateral view of same specimen as in (B). Scale bars: 100 mm (A); 150 mm (B, C); 120 mm (D)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4581403/files/figure.png" .

